block.p: Kathleen Mary Collins, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Timothy F. Collins III of Walpole, Mass., was married yesterday to Tucker Matthew Walsh, a son of Mr. and Mrs. E. Stephen Walsh of Mount Vernon, N.Y. The Rev. John P. Culloty, a Roman Catholic priest, performed the ceremony at St. Timothy's Church in Norwood, Mass.
Mrs. Walsh, 27, teaches at the Old South Preschool in Boston. She graduated from the University of New Hampshire.

Kathleen Mary Collins, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Timothy F. Collins III of Walpole, Mass., was married yesterday to Tucker Matthew Walsh, a son of Mr. and Mrs. E. Stephen Walsh of Mount Vernon, N.Y. The Rev. John P. Culloty, a Roman Catholic priest, performed the ceremony at St. Timothy's Church in Norwood, Mass.
Mrs. Walsh, 27, teaches at the Old South Preschool in Boston. She graduated from the University of New Hampshire.
Mr. Walsh, 30, is a vice president and portfolio manager at State Street Research and Management, the investment management company in Boston. He graduated from Washington and Lee University.
